    <h3 id="standout" class="p-3 my-4 rounded-3 text-center border border-success border-4" style="font-size:larger; background-color: red;color:white;"><strong>Permanent ceasefire!
            End the occupation!</strong></h3>
            <p id="standout"><em>Protest alone is not sufficient, but it is necessary in order to promote public awareness and support
                    for a permanent ceasefire, an end to the Israeli occupation and US military aid to Israel, and to challenge the
                    climate of neo-McCarthyist  repression that falsely equates opposition to Israel's genocidal war on Gaza with antisemitism.</em></p>
    <p>MV For Palestine holds standouts in solidarity with the Palestinian cause at the Five Corners intersection in Vineyard Haven every Sunday, rain or shine. Come join us!
        Our next standout at Five Corners will be <strong>{{ standout.nextStandoutDate }}</strong>.</p>
    <img src="{{ asset('images/17-dec.5-corners.jpg') }}" alt="MV For Palestine members standing on the sidewalk holding signs demanding a ceasefire" class="img-fluid mb-3">
    <p>We've been out there every Sunday since November 19, 2023. Anyone who shares our goals -- stop the genocide in Gaza, fight the big lie that equates criticism of Zionism with antisemitism --
    is welcome to join us in this weekly demonstration. We stay for {{ standout.duration_informal }}, but you can arrive late or leave early if need be. If you
    don't bring a sign, you can borrow one from our supply. If you aren't comfortable standing, you can bring a chair or use one of ours. Public restrooms are available within easy
        walking distance at the Vineyard Haven ferry terminal. Whether you're a year-round resident, seasonal, or just on the island for a day trip -- join us!
    </p>

            <h2 class="text-center">other actions and events</h2>
            <p>Have an idea about something MV For Palestine could do to further its objectives? Feel free to
                <a href="/join">join us</a> and propose your idea.</p>
    </div>
